{
  "stem": "11844.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Here is that stupid guy who is not even a German-- come from Austria-- and he has the nerve, speaking in poor German with a terrible accent, and tell people that the Jews are the misfortune of Germany, and we are not Germans, and we don't belong here.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my family lived in Germany maybe for 1,500 years, probably.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there were Jewish communities in Germany in the entire area where the Romans came.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That means southwest Germany and western Germany, along the Rhine River, the Danube, and so on.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And here, that guy is telling all those terrible things.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I never felt scared.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I never felt threatened.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I thought it won't take very long.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The German people got to get wise to that person.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And, of course, that changed in 1938 after Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But till that time, I was angry, and rightly so.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I wouldn't say everybody else, no.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "After all, there was a very strong [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Jewish emigration out of Germany.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were a little bit over 600,000 Jews lived in Germany when Hitler became chancellor, and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] beginning of the war, '39, in August or July, there were between 50,000 to 300,000.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So half of the German Jews left Germany as emigrants between-- the emigration was very strong in '33.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Strong in '34, '35, '36.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A little '37 increasing. '38, very strong.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And '39-- couldn't get out anymore after July anyway.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So my personal attitude was not necessarily typical for all German Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I read while I was doing some research that in '33 a lot of the Jews from Germany to the Netherlands, but in '34-- '34 was relatively quiet as far as anti-Semitic actions, and a lot of Jews returned to Germany.",
      "word_count": 41
    }
  ],
